"/> There was a silver maker by the name of Jabez Gorham (b1792-d.1869) who
produced silver in Providence, R.I. from 1813-1847. His items were marked J
Gorham. The only Gorham producing silver during the time frame you mention was
Miles Gorham but his silver was marked either MG in a wavy rectangle or M
Gorham in a rectangle. This really doesn't answer your question, I realize but
have you considered going to one of the geneological web sites and putting in
either of those names? Also, is there any other mark on the piece besides
&quot;Gorham&quot;?

